    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - 2 SPEED REAR AXLES: SPICER - REMOVE</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>REMOVE</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="2">
            <title>DIFFERENTIAL CARRIER</title>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Steam clean axle assembly before removing carrier.</para>
                    <para>Wheel ends may have one bolt replacing a stud. This is thru-drilled into the cavity and can be
                        used to drain and fill the wheel end.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Block wheels.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Shift the axle into low range.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Drain lubricant from axle housing.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove axle shift unit from carrier assembly.</para>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>Shift unit contains lubricant. Provide container to catch lubricant.</para>
                        <para>For servicing the shift unit, refer to GROUP 14 - REAR AXLE in the CTS-5000 Master Service
                            Manual.
                        </para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect drive shaft at rear U-joint. Refer to GROUP 06 - PROPELLER SHAFTS in the
                    CTS-5000 Master Service Manual for the correct procedure to remove the shafts.
                </para>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>If ring or pinion bearings are to be removed, break loose pinion nut at this time.</para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the axle shaft flange nuts.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Hold a large brass drift or brass hammer against the center of the axle shaft flange.
                    Strike the drift with sharp blows from a large hammer or sledge until axle shaft separates from hub.
                </para>
                <specpara>
                    <warning>
                        <para>Do not strike the axle flange directly with a steel hammer or sledge. This may crack and
                            splinter material, possibly causing serious or fatal injury. Do not pry or chisel axle
                            flange away from hub or damage to sealing surfaces could occur.
                        </para>
                    </warning>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove axle shafts.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Support carrier assembly on roller jack. Secure as necessary to prevent carrier from
                    falling from jack when removed from housing.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove differential carrier-to-axle housing bolts.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Break carrier loose from housing with the use of pry bars behind carrier flange mounting
                    face (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1401504">Figure 4</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f1401504" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1401504" filename="../figg14/g1401504.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="272px" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 4. Carrier Housing Removal</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove carrier from housing.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Mount carrier assembly in suitable rebuild stand (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1401505">Figure 5</hotlnk>). Refer to
                    <hotlnk document="s14015_39.xml" xrefid="hl1401501">SPECIAL TOOLS
                        <xref refid="hl1401501"/>
                    </hotlnk>
                    .
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f1401505" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1401505" filename="../figg14/g1401505.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="272px" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 5. Carrier Mounted in Rebuild Stand</caption>
            </figure>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
